 Parameters: `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `env_vars`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`\n  - Validate `workload_manager_url` and `router_url` (param or env)\n  - Build AgentRuntime CR spec\n  - Create CR via `create_namespaced_custom_object()`\n  - Handle 409 conflict with `replace_namespaced_custom_object()`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verify: CR created/updated, returns status dict\n\n- [x] **T1.6** Implement `_sanitize_name()` helper\n  - Lowercase, replace non-alphanumeric with `-`\n  - Collapse multiple dashes, strip leading/trailing\n  - Truncate to 63 chars max\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Produces valid K8s names (e.g., \"My-Agent!\" → \"my-agent\")\n\n- [x] **T1.7** Implement `get_agent_runtime()` method\n  - Get AgentRuntime CR by name\n  - Return None on 404, raise on other errors\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Returns CR dict or None\n\n- [x] **T1.8** Implement `wait_for_deployment_ready()` method\n  - Poll CR status.conditions for Ready=True\n  - Timeout after specified seconds (default 120)\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Returns when ready, raises TimeoutError on timeout\n\n- [x] **T1.9** Implement `get_agent_runtime_status()` method\n  - Extract phase, conditions, agentEndpoint from CR status\n  - Return formatted status dict\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Returns status with phase, endpoint, conditions\n\n- [x] **T1.10** Implement `delete_agent_runtime()` method\n  - Delete CR via `delete_namespaced_custom_object()`\n  - Return status dict, handle 404 gracefully\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verify: CR deleted, returns status\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: KubernetesProvider Service Implementation ✓\n\n- [x] **T2.1** Create `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` file\n  - Import kubernetes client with availability check\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Module imports successfully\n\n- [x] **T2.2** Implement `KubernetesProvider.__init__()`\n  - Parameters: `namespace`, `verbose`, `kubeconfig`\n  - Initialize `_core_v1 = CoreV1Api()`, `_apps_v1 = AppsV1Api()`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Instantiates with API clients\n\n- [x] **T2.3** Implement `_load_config()` method\n  - Same pattern as AgentCubeProvider\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Loads kubeconfig or in-cluster\n\n- [x] **T2.4** Implement `_ensure_namespace()` method\n  - Same pattern as AgentCubeProvider\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Creates namespace if needed\n\n- [x] **T2.5** Implement `deploy_agent()` method\n  - Parameters: `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `replicas`, `node_port`, `env_vars`\n  - Create Deployment + Service\n  - Wait for deployment ready\n  - Return deployment info dict\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Deployment + Service created, returns info\n\n- [x] **T2.6** Implement `_create_deployment()` method\n  - Build V1Deployment spec with container, env vars, replicas\n  - Handle 409 with replace\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Deployment created/updated\n\n- [x] **T2.7** Implement `_create_service()` method\n  - Build V1Service with NodePort type\n  - Handle 409 with replace\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Service created with correct node_port\n\n- [x] **T2.8** Implement `wait_for_deployment_ready()` method\n  - Poll deployment status.ready_replicas\n  - Timeout after specified seconds\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Returns when ready, raises TimeoutError\n\n- [x] **T2.9** Implement `get_agent_status()` method\n  - Read deployment, extract replica counts\n  - Return status dict\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Returns running/not_found status\n\n- [x] **T2.10** Implement `delete_agent()` method\n  - Delete deployment and service\n  - Handle 404 gracefully\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Resources deleted\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: PublishRuntime Integration ✓\n\n- [x] **T3.1** Import providers in `publish_runtime.py`\n  - Import `AgentCubeProvider`, `KubernetesProvider`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Imports successful\n\n- [x] **T3.2** Add `provider` parameter to `PublishRuntime.__init__()`\n  - Default: `\"agentcube\"`\n  - Store as `self.provider`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Runtime accepts provider parameter\n\n- [x] **T3.3** Implement `_validate_publish_prerequisites()` for AgentCube\n  - Check `workload_manager_url` and `router_url` in metadata\n  - Raise `ValueError` with helpful message if missing\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Validates URLs before deployment\n\n- [x] **T3.4** Implement `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` method\n  - Instantiate `AgentCubeProvider`\n  - Call `deploy_agent_runtime()` with metadata fields\n  - Call `wait_for_deployment_ready()`\n  - Call `get_agent_runtime_status()`\n  - Generate `session_id`, `agent_id`\n  - Return deployment info dict\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Returns complete deployment info\n\n- [x] **T3.5** Implement `_publish_k8s()` method\n  - Instantiate `KubernetesProvider`\n  - Validate `node_port` range (30000-32767)\n  - Call `deploy_agent()` with metadata fields\n  - Call `wait_for_deployment_ready()`\n  - Generate `session_id`\n  - Return deployment info dict\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Returns deployment + service info\n\n- [x] **T3.6** Implement `_build_agent_env_vars()` helper\n  - Extract `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `agent_endpoint` from metadata\n  - Return env dict\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Returns correct env vars\n\n- [x] **T3.7** Update `publish()` method to route by provider\n  - If `provider == \"agentcube\"`: call `_publish_cr_to_k8s()`\n  - If `provider == \"k8s\"`: call `_publish_k8s()`\n  - Else: raise `ValueError`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct provider selected\n\n- [x] **T3.8** Implement `_update_publish_metadata()` method\n  - Update: `agent_id`, `session_id`, `agent_endpoint`, `image`, `k8s_deployment`\n  - Call `metadata_service.save_metadata()`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Metadata persisted after publish\n\n- [x] **T3.9** Implement `_generate_session_id()` helper\n  - Generate 32-char alphanumeric using `secrets.choice()`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Returns unique ID each call\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: CLI Integration ✓\n\n- [x] **T4.1** Add `provider` option to `publish` command\n  - `--provider` with default \"agentcube\"\n  - Help text: \"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Option accepted, shown in --help\n\n- [x] **T4.2** Add `node_port` option to `publish` command\n  - `--node-port` (optional int)\n  - Help text: \"Specific NodePort (30000-32767)\"\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Option accepted\n\n- [x] **T4.3** Add `replicas` option to `publish` command\n  - `--replicas` (optional int, default 1)\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Option accepted\n\n- [x] **T4.4** Add `namespace` option to `publish` command\n  - `--namespace` (optional string)\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Option accepted\n\n- [x] **T4.5** Pass provider to `PublishRuntime` constructor\n  - `runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Provider parameter passed through\n\n- [x] **T4.6** Pass all options to `runtime.publish()`\n  - Include: `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Options dict complete\n\n- [x] **T4.7** Format output for AgentCube provider\n  - Show: Router URL, Workload Manager, Endpoint\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: AgentCube-specific fields displayed\n\n- [x] **T4.8** Format output for K8s provider\n  - Show: Deployment, Service, NodePort, Service URL, Replicas\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: K8s-specific fields displayed\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Validation & Edge Cases ✓\n\n- [x] **T5.1** Validate `workload_manager_url` and `router_url` for agentcube\n  - Check in metadata or raise ValueError\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Clear error message when URLs missing\n\n- [x] **T5.2** Validate `node_port` range (30000-32767)\n  - Validate in `_publish_k8s()` before provider call\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Rejects 29999 and 32768\n\n- [x] **T5.3** Handle existing AgentRuntime CR (409 conflict)\n  - Use `replace_namespaced_custom_object()` on 409\n  - Log update vs create\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Existing CR updated gracefully\n\n- [x] **T5.4** Handle existing Deployment/Service (409 conflict)\n  - Use `replace_namespaced_deployment()` and `replace_namespaced_service()`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verify: Existing resources updated\n\n- [x] **T5.5** Handle missing K8s config gracefully\n  - Try kubeconfig, then in-cluster, then raise RuntimeError\n  - File: Both providers\n  - Verify: Clear error when K8s unavailable\n\n- [x] **T5.6** Handle image push failures\n  - DockerService exceptions caught and re-raised with context\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Error message includes context\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Unit Tests ✓\n\n- [x] **T6.1** Test `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()`\n  - Mock kubernetes API, verify CR spec\n  - Test with/without workload_manager_url\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct CR created\n\n- [x] **T6.2** Test `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()`\n  - Mock kubernetes API, verify Deployment/Service spec\n  - Test node_port parameter\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct resources created\n\n- [x] **T6.3** Test `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()`\n  - Mock `AgentCubeProvider`, verify method calls\n  - Verify session_id generated\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Provider called correctly\n\n- [x] **T6.4** Test `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s()`\n  - Mock `KubernetesProvider`, verify method calls\n  - Verify node_port validated\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Provider called correctly\n\n- [x] **T6.5** Test node_port validation\n  - Test values: 29999, 30000, 32767, 32768\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Rejects out-of-range, accepts valid\n\n- [x] **T6.6** Test missing URLs for agentcube\n  - Call publish without workload_manager_url\n  - Verify ValueError with helpful message\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Clear error message\n\n- [x] **T6.7** Test provider routing\n  - Test provider=\"agentcube\" routes to CR method\n  - Test provider=\"k8s\" routes to K8s method\n  - Test provider=\"invalid\" raises ValueError\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct routing logic\n\n- [x] **T6.8** Test metadata update after publish\n  - Mock publish, verify metadata fields updated\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: agent_id, session_id, endpoint saved\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Code Quality ✓\n\n- [x] **T7.1** Add docstrings to all public methods\n  - Document parameters, returns, raises\n  - File: Both providers, publish_runtime.py\n  - Verify: `help()` displays correctly\n\n- [x] **T7.2** Add type hints to all functions\n  - Use `typing` module for complex types\n  - File: All provider and runtime files\n  - Verify: mypy passes\n\n- [x] **T7.3** Run ruff linting\n  - Command: `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/`\n  - Fix all lint errors\n  - Verify: No ruff errors\n\n- [x] **T7.4** Run pytest with coverage\n  - Command: `pytest --cov=agentcube cmd/cli/tests/`\n  - Verify coverage >= 80%\n  - Verify: All methods tested\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. ✅ `AgentCubeProvider` implements deploy/get/wait/delete for AgentRuntime CR\n2. ✅ `KubernetesProvider` implements deploy/get/wait/delete for Deployment/Service\n3. ✅ AgentCubeProvider validates workload_manager_url and router_url\n4. ✅ KubernetesProvider validates node_port range (30000-32767)\n5. ✅ PublishRuntime routes to correct provider based on `provider` parameter\n6. ✅ 409 conflicts handled gracefully (update vs create)\n7. ✅ Missing K8s config produces clear error message\n8. ✅ CLI `publish` command accepts --provider, --node-port, --replicas, --namespace\n9. ✅ Output formatted correctly for both providers\n10. ✅ Metadata updated with publish results (agent_id, session_id, endpoint)\n11. ✅ Unit tests cover all provider methods and validation logic\n12. ✅ Type hints pass mypy validation\n13. ✅ Code passes ruff linting\n14. ✅ Test coverage >= 80%\n\n---\n\n**Notes:**\n- Stage ST-3 marked complete: all providers and runtime implemented\n- Both AgentCubeProvider and KubernetesProvider fully functional\n- CLI publish command supports both providers\n- All validation and error handling in place\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/service